---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'IMG Global in Colombia', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-img', text: 'Why IMG for Colombia', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-details', text: 'Coverage Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Who It\'s Best For', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Colombia', href: '/countries/colombia/insurance' },
  { title: 'IMG Global Review', href: '/providers/img-global' },
  { title: 'IMG vs SafetyWing', href: '/compare/img-global-vs-safetywing' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price (Age 35)' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Global Medical Insurance', coverage: 'Inpatient + outpatient', price: '$100-150/mo' },
  { plan: 'Global Medical Insurance Plus', coverage: 'Comprehensive', price: '$150-180/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="IMG Global Health Insurance in Colombia"
  description="Guide to IMG Global international health insurance for expats in Colombia. Flexible, affordable coverage for digital nomads and long-term expats."
  headline="IMG Global in Colombia"
  subheadline="Flexible international coverage at competitive prices. Popular choice for Colombia's digital nomad and expat community."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/colombia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an IMG Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/img-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">IMG Global in Colombia</h2>
  <p>
    IMG Global offers a strong middle ground between budget travel insurance and premium international health plans. For Colombia expats who want comprehensive coverage without paying top-tier prices, IMG delivers excellent value.
  </p>
  <p>
    With flexible plan options and competitive pricing, IMG has become popular among digital nomads and expats throughout Latin America, including Colombia's growing remote worker community.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$100-180</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Monthly (Age 35)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Flexible</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Customizable plans</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Good Value</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Competitive pricing</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your IMG Colombia Quote"
    description="Flexible coverage at competitive prices for Colombia expats."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/img-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="why-img">Why IMG for Colombia</h2>
  <p>
    IMG Global works well for Colombia expats for several reasons:
  </p>

  <h3>Price-Performance Balance</h3>
  <p>
    IMG sits in the sweet spot between budget options (like SafetyWing) and premium insurers (like Cigna). You get comprehensive coverage—including outpatient benefits—at prices that don't break the bank.
  </p>

  <h3>Plan Flexibility</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Multiple deductible options ($0 to $25,000)</li>
    <li>Choose your coverage area (regional or worldwide)</li>
    <li>Add or exclude specific benefits</li>
    <li>Annual or semi-annual payment options</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Digital Nomad Friendly</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Meets Colombia visa requirements</li>
    <li>Easy online enrollment and management</li>
    <li>Coverage continues while traveling</li>
    <li>Portable if you relocate</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Hospital Network</h3>
  <p>
    IMG works with major hospitals throughout Colombia:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Bogotá:</strong> Access to Fundación Santa Fe, Clínica del Country</li>
    <li><strong>Medellín:</strong> Coverage at Las Américas, Pablo Tobón Uribe</li>
    <li><strong>Other cities:</strong> Network access in Cartagena, Cali, Barranquilla</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 italic">
    Prices shown for healthy 35-year-old. Actual premiums depend on age, health history, selected coverage, and deductible.
  </p>

  <h3>Cost Factors</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Deductible:</strong> Big impact on premiums—$2,500 deductible can reduce costs 30%+</li>
    <li><strong>Age:</strong> Premiums increase with age</li>
    <li><strong>Coverage area:</strong> Americas-only vs worldwide</li>
    <li><strong>US coverage:</strong> Including US adds to premiums</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">High-Deductible Strategy</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      In Colombia, where routine care is affordable, a high-deductible IMG plan makes sense. Pay out-of-pocket for GP visits and minor issues, let insurance handle expensive hospitalizations and emergencies.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="coverage-details">Coverage Details</h2>

  <h3>What's Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Inpatient:</strong> Hospital stays, surgery, ICU</li>
    <li><strong>Outpatient:</strong> Doctor visits, specialists, diagnostics</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency:</strong> Worldwide emergency coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Medical evacuation included</li>
    <li><strong>Prescription drugs:</strong> Outpatient medications covered</li>
    <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Coverage included (with limits)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions: 12-month exclusion period</li>
    <li>Maternity: Optional, requires waiting period</li>
    <li>Dental: Limited benefits, better as standalone</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Who It's Best For</h2>

  <h3>Digital Nomads</h3>
  <p>
    IMG's combination of comprehensive coverage, reasonable pricing, and flexibility makes it ideal for digital nomads based in Colombia. It meets visa requirements and provides peace of mind without the premium insurer price tag.
  </p>

  <h3>Cost-Conscious Expats</h3>
  <p>
    If you want more than basic travel insurance but don't need (or want to pay for) premium coverage, IMG hits the sweet spot. The coverage is solid, and the price is right.
  </p>

  <h3>Medium-term Stays</h3>
  <p>
    For expats planning to stay in Colombia for 1-5 years, IMG provides appropriate coverage without locking you into premium long-term commitments.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare IMG Plans for Colombia"
    description="Find flexible coverage at the right price."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/img-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Prices and coverage details are estimates based on typical scenarios. Get a personalized quote for accurate pricing based on your age, health, and coverage needs.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
